                          Embedly - JQuery - An OEmbed Library to Replace Links with Content

  What is it?
  -----------

  Embedly - JQuery is a JQuery Library for Embedly that will replace links with content.
  It follows the oEmbed spec (http://oembed.com) for content 
  retrieval, while utilizing http://api.embed.ly as a single endpoint.

  This is the JQuery portion of Embedly.

  Documentation
  -------------

  The most up-to-date documentation can be found at http://github.com/embedly/embedly-jquery/raw/master/README

  Requirements
  -----------------------------------------

  Requires JQuery 1.4.1 or greater
  Requires jquery.embedly.js

  <script type="text/javascript" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.4.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
  <script type="text/javascript" src="http://github.com/embedly/embedly-jquery/raw/master/jquery.embedly.js"></script>
  
  Using Embedly-JQuery
  -----------------------------------------

    * There are two ways to interact with this library. 

        * Call directly - ( Returns json object representing oembed or null. )

            * $.embedly('http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LfamTmY5REw', {}, function(oembed){ alert(oembed.title);});

            * $.embedly('http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LfamTmY5REw', {maxWidth:600, maxHeight:400}, function(oembed){ alert(oembed.title);});  // with maxWidth option set to 600px and maxHeight option set to 400px

        * Use a CSS selector to replace every valid link with an embed on the page. (Replaces links for you)

            *  $('a').embedly();

            *  $('a').embedly({maxWidth:600});  // with maxWidth option set to 600px

            *  $('a').embedly({maxWidth:600, method:'after'});  // with maxWidth option set to 600px and method option set to 'after'

            *  $('a').embedly({maxWidth:600, urlRe: /http:\/\/(www\.hulu\.com\/watch.*)/i, method:'after'});  // with maxWidth option set to 600px and method option set to 'after' and urlRe option set for only hulu.com videos

    * Valid Options
         
        * maxWidth - a number representing the "max width" in pixels a piece of content can be displayed in your page. (Default : original width of the content)    
         
        * maxHeight - a number representing the "max height" in pixels a piece of content can be displayed in your page. (Default : original height of the content) 
         
        * urlRe = a regular expression representing what links to show content for. (Default : all available Embedly sources, see http://api.embed.ly)     
                   Use : http://api.embed.ly/tools/generator to generate regular expressions for a specific set of sources.
         
        * method - a string value either "replace" or "after" to tell Embedly how to place the content in your page. (Default : 'replace')
                    replace - replaces the link with the content.
                    after - inserts the content after the link.
                    afterParent - inserts the content after the parent element.   
        
        * wrapElement - a string value representing the valid html element to wrap the content in. (Default : 'div')
 
        * className - a string value representing a CSS class you would like to assign to the wrapElement. (Default : 'embed')
 
        * addImageStyles - a boolean value representing whether or not Embedly should use the style element to resize images based on the maxWidth and maxHeight parameters (Default : true)

  Examples
  -----------------------------------------
  Examples can be found at - http://github.com/embedly/embedly-jquery/tree/master/examples/
  
